olive oil
1 packet salmon
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 courgette
2 clove garlic
1 packet broccoli florets
drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

• In a medium bowl, combine salmon, garlic & herb seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
• When pan is hot, cook salmon, skin-side down first, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes each side.
• Transfer to serving plates, season and cover to keep warm.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice courgette into sticks. Finely chop garlic.

• Wipe out frying pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook broccoli florets and courgette until tender, 5-6 minutes.
• Add garlic and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar, and cook, until fragrant, 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper.

TIP: Add a dash of water to the pan to help speed up the cooking process.

• Divide garlic greens between plates with herby salmon. Serve with dill & parsley mayonnaise. Enjoy!